1 AN ACT relating to the home installation credit.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 141 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Eligible individual" means any individual living in the Commonwealth
7 who:
8 1. Is age sixty-five (65) or older; or
9 2. Has a physical or mental impairment that substantially limits one (1)
10 or more of a person's major life activities and has lasted or can be
11 expected to last for a continuous period of not less than twelve (12)
12 months;
13 (b) "Energy efficient" denotes improvements made to a qualifying residence
14 that include building products, heating and cooling systems, or water
15 heaters affixed with the energy star label having been certified as meeting
16 energy efficiency criteria by the United States Environmental Protection
17 Agency and the United States Department of Energy;
18 (c) "Qualifying home installation" means any upgrade or modification made to
19 a qualifying residence that increases its habitability, efficiency, or
20 accessibility for a resident, including dependents, of the dwelling and shall
21 be products that are:
22 1. Energy efficient; or
23 2. Composed of sustainable materials;
24 (d) "Qualifying residence" means the eligible individual's primary dwelling
25 located within the Commonwealth; and
26 (e) "Sustainable" means a product that has a low environmental impact and
27 contains recyclable and renewable components.
