1 (2) For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, but before January 1,
2 2030, an eligible individual who makes a qualifying home installation to his or
3 her qualifying residence may claim a credit that shall:
4 (a) Be equal to the actual cost of the qualifying home installation expenses
5 incurred;
6 (b) Not exceed seven thousand five hundred dollars ($7,500) for each taxable
7 year within which a qualifying home installation is made; and
8 (c) Be refundable and claimed as a credit against the tax computed under KRS
9 141.020.
10 (3) (a) The purpose of the home installation credit is to assist eligible individuals
11 with the cost of upgrading their homes to make them more accessible or
12 energy efficient.
13 (b) In order for the General Assembly to evaluate the effectiveness of the home
14 installation credit, the department shall report the following information to
15 the Interim Joint Committee on Appropriations and Revenue on or before
16 December 1, 2027, and on or before each December 1 thereafter, as long as
17 the credit is claimed on a tax return:
18 1. The number of returns claiming the home installation credit;
19 2. The total amount of credit claimed for each taxable year; and
20 3. Based on ranges of adjusted gross income of no larger than five
21 thousand dollars ($5,000), the total amount of credit claimed and the
22 number of returns claiming a credit for each adjusted gross income
23 range for each taxable year.
